casebody.data:
AMERICAN STORES COMPANY v. EDWIN J. ELMORE. [No. 59,

October Term, 1933.]

Decided December 7th, 1933.

The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Pattison, Ubner, Adkins, Dictaras, Parke, and Sloan, JJ.

Cr. Randolph Aiken, submitting on brief, for the appellant. Richard H. Stevenson, with whom was Edwin Webster Wells on the brief, for the appellee.

The opinion was delivered

per Curiam.
